parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
and may not respond to braking. The acceleration can occur at various speeds
and may be accompanied by a sudden increase in engine RPM.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Accelerator Pedal and Electronic Throttle Control System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal and electronic throttle control system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal may stick or fail to return to its normal position
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly. The electronic throttle control system may malfunction
leading to sudden acceleration or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may not respond to braking. The brakes may fail to engage
or the vehicle may accelerate despite braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leakage can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially cause accidents due to loss of control.
symptoms: oil puddles under the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden engine stalling can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: loss of power steering and brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the emissions system can cause environmental harm and potentially lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: sulfur smell from the exhaust system.
